Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for ~{12%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Lay the @salmon{200%g}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, add half the garlic and lightly season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Rub to coat evenly.

Scatter the @sesame seeds{1%sachet} over the top.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish. Fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Cut the @broccoli{1%head} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the broccoli for ~{2-3%minutes}, add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and cover with a lid or some foil. Cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Transfer the broccoli to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Pop the pan back on medium-high heat.

Stir @water{75%ml} (double for 4p), @red Thai style paste{1%sachet}, @ketjap manis{1%sachet} and @honey{2%sachets} into the pan.

Bring to the boil and cook until reduced by half, ~{3-5%minutes}. Once reduced, remove from the heat.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir @butter{1%tbsp} (double for 4p) into the sauce.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lime juice.

Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if required.

Once ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Share the zesty lime rice between #bowls{}.

Top with the sesame salmon, spooning over the sauce from the pan.

Serve the broccoli alongside.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges and serve on the side for squeezing over.